00:01:44.120 --> 00:01:44.665
swimming around.

00:01:44.665 --> 00:01:47.310
So one of the things that I like
to do for donations is I

00:01:47.310 --> 00:01:48.380
like to have a bag.

00:01:48.380 --> 00:01:50.870
For instance, this tote bag,
because it's easy to carry.

00:01:50.870 --> 00:01:53.230
I just put my donations
in here.

00:01:53.230 --> 00:01:54.650
It lives by the door.

00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:56.940
And then when it gets full
or I know I'm going by my

00:01:56.940 --> 00:02:00.000
favorite place to donate,
I grab it, and it goes.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.990
And then that way, you have
a place for everything and

00:02:02.990 --> 00:02:03.670
everything in its place.

00:02:03.670 --> 00:02:04.960
These things don't live
on your desk.

00:02:04.960 --> 00:02:06.060
They live in this bag.

00:02:06.060 --> 00:02:06.580
SALLY HORCHOW: OK.

00:02:06.580 --> 00:02:07.550
Exactly.

00:02:07.550 --> 00:02:08.419
So everything in its place.

00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:09.520
Now this is a file.

00:02:09.520 --> 00:02:10.509
It's all one trip.

00:02:10.509 --> 00:02:12.200
It's a travel file.

00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:14.310
I even have a place
for this to go.

00:02:14.310 --> 00:02:16.060
It goes in the file cabinet.

